    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\npressing `<c-d>` results in multiple command lines being rendered on the screen (can be cleared via `<c-l>`)\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/20a65960-73e4-4c70-bbf3-2e08d46655f9\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. minimal.lua\n\n```lua\nvim.cmd.edit(\"$VIMRUNTIME/doc/help.txt\")\n\n-- require(\"vim._extui\").enable({})\n\nvim.schedule(function()\n\tvim.api.nvim_open_win(\n\t\t0,\n\t\ttrue,\n\t\t{\n\t\t\trelative = \"editor\",\n\t\t\tanchor = \"NW\",\n\t\t\tborder = \"none\",\n\t\t\trow = 0,\n\t\t\tcol = 0,\n\t\t\twidth = vim.o.columns,\n\t\t\theight = vim.o.lines,\n\t\t\t-- style = \"minimal\",\n\t\t}\n\t)\nend)\n```\n\n2. run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n3. press `<c-d><c-d>...`\n\n(but rendering works correctly whe `vim._extui` is enabled)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno rendering error\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-604+g5ea6a022c0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.15.2-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Removing this ` - MAX(rows, 0)` seems to fix the problem:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c b/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\nindex 37aa964ad4..4e66e35a94 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\n@@ -669,7 +669,7 @@ void ui_comp_grid_scroll(Integer grid, Integer top, Integer bot, Integer left, I\n   bot += curgrid->comp_row;\n   left += curgrid->comp_col;\n   right += curgrid->comp_col;\n-  bool covered = curgrid_covered_above((int)(bot - MAX(rows, 0)));\n+  bool covered = curgrid_covered_above((int)bot);\n \n   if (covered || curgrid->blending) {\n     // TODO(bfredl):\n```\nbut I don't know what it's supposed to do.",
